      name="BCA Lifestyle: Movie Vertical"
      desc="Nov 2019 – Apr 2020"
    >
      <p class="pb-2 text-justify text-sm text-tapa-500">
        I developed the front-end web interface and integrated the movie ticket
        vertical, using popular JavaScript libraries such as ReactJS, Redux
        (with Redux Thunk middleware), React I18n, React Router, Axios, and
        Webpack. The app communicates with the underlying service through REST
        APIs.
      </p>
      <p class="pb-2 text-justify indent-4 text-sm text-tapa-500">
        Within the app, users can buy movie tickets online in a few easy steps.
        Users browse the movie they want to watch and select the cinema
        location, the showtime, and the seat location. Then the user will see a
        checkout page showing the purchase details. The payment process will ask
        the users for their PIN and the amount will be deducted directly from
        the bank account balance. The movie tickets can be redeemed at the
        cinema using the code shown on the app.
      </p>
      <p class="pb-2 text-justify indent-4 text-sm text-tapa-500">
        The movie ticket vertical integration takes about six months. I worked
        with a front-end team that consisted of three people: a senior software
        engineer and two other software engineers. I communicated with the
        product managers, UI/UX staff, and quality assurance team members to
        ensure my deliverables fulfilled the requirements.
      </p>

